<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[192,1441,419,699]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,355,419,443]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Description</emphasis>
. Size moderate to large, length 
<quantity box="[745,917,419,443]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.3" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="2.7">2.7 to 5.3 mm</quantity>
. Clypeal apex flat, truncate or emarginate, surface tuberculate (
<figureCitation box="[453,548,451,475]" captionStart="Figures 5" captionStartId="60.[192,286,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[212,1422,211,1647]" captionTargetId="figure-17@60.[192,1440,192,1667]" captionTargetPageId="60" captionText="Figures 5A-5G. Glaresis montenegro, new species. A) Habitus view. B) Clypeus and head surface. D) Metasternum and mesotibia. C) Pronotal surface. E) Male genitalia. F) Metaleg and trochanter, dorsal view. G) Metaleg and trochanter, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4645631" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4645631/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[564,600,451,475]" captionStart="Figures 6" captionStartId="61.[192,287,1671,1693]" captionTargetBox="[209,1411,206,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-16@61.[192,1440,192,1655]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Figures 6A-6H. Glaresis yanegai, new species. A) Habitus view. B) Clypeus and head surface. C) Pronotal surface. D) Metasternum and mesotibia. E) Elytral striae. F) Male genitalia. G) Metaleg and trochanter, dorsal view. H) Metaleg and trochanter, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4645633" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4645633/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">6B</figureCitation>
). Pronotal fovea absent or weakly impressed. Elytral striae not to weakly carinate. Metasternum with surface ridges unmodified, metasternal groove not visible or difficult to detect. Mesotibia with strong apical projection, posterolateral emargination with 4-9 spines (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Dyke. A" authorityYear="1928" box="[1310,1440,515,539]" class="Insecta" family="Glaresidae" genus="Glaresis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[1310,1331,516,539]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1343,1440,515,539]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may have more than 5 spines). Posterior metatrochanteral margin without teeth, or lateral angle with single tooth. Lateral metatibial margin not apically incised, with small, more or less even teeth, lacking a major posteromedian lateral projection (except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Dyke. A" authorityYear="1928" box="[801,937,611,635]" class="Insecta" family="Glaresidae" genus="Glaresis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[801,822,612,635]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[838,937,611,635]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Apex of 5th female abdominal ventrite notched or weakly emarginate medially (except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Dyke. A" authorityYear="1928" box="[774,909,643,667]" class="Insecta" family="Glaresidae" genus="Glaresis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[774,795,644,667]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[810,909,643,667]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), male ventrite apically truncate or slightly arcuate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[192,1441,739,828]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,315,739,763]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Remarks</emphasis>
. This group contains 6 species, all except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Dyke. A" authorityYear="1928" box="[816,950,739,763]" class="Insecta" family="Glaresidae" genus="Glaresis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[816,837,740,763]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[851,950,739,763]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially very similar in appearance. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Van Dyke. A" authorityYear="1928" box="[192,396,771,795]" class="Insecta" family="Glaresidae" genus="Glaresis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[192,396,771,795]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Glaresis clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is atypical of this group, but is placed here because it is more similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fall. A" authorityYear="1907" box="[1243,1389,771,795]" class="Insecta" family="Glaresidae" genus="Glaresis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenicis">
<emphasis box="[1243,1264,772,795]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1276,1389,771,795]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">phoenicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and allies than to any other group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1848" box="[593,694,803,827]" class="Insecta" family="Glaresidae" genus="Glaresis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[593,694,803,827]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Glaresis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
